{#
  Landing page for https://bauer-group.github.io/XPD-RPIImage/
  (flips to a custom domain once site/CNAME + DNS are in place - the
  catalog_url is resolved at render time by the pages workflow).

  Rendered by scripts/build_pages.py with Jinja2 (autoescape on). All
  variables come from manifests[] + repo/tag/catalog_url/generated.
#}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>BAUER GROUP RPIImage – latest release {{ tag }}</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Declarative, reproducible Raspberry Pi OS images by BAUER GROUP. RPi Imager catalog + direct downloads." />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="logo.svg" />
</head>
<body>
  <header class="hero">
    <div class="inner">
      <img src="logo-wide-white.svg" alt="BAUER GROUP" class="logo" />
      <h1>📦 <span class="accent">RPIImage</span></h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Declarative, reproducible, CI-built Raspberry Pi OS images for production and development.</p>
      <p class="release">Current release:
        <a href="https://github.com/{{ repo }}/releases/tag/{{ tag }}"><strong>{{ tag }}</strong></a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="pitch">
      <h2>🛠 Add this repo to Raspberry Pi Imager</h2>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>Install <a href="https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/">Raspberry Pi Imager</a> (v1.8.5 or later).</li>
        <li>Open it and go to <strong>Settings</strong> (the ⚙ icon) → <strong>Custom repository</strong>.</li>
        <li>Paste the catalog URL below and close the settings dialog:
          <div class="copyrow">
            <code id="catalog-url">{{ catalog_url }}</code>
            <button type="button" onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText(document.getElementById('catalog-url').innerText)">Copy</button>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>Restart Imager. Our variants now appear under <strong>Operating System → BAUER GROUP</strong>.</li>
        <li>Pick your target device → pick an image → flash.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>🧷 Flashing a Compute Module (CM4 / CM5 eMMC)</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Put the carrier board in <strong>rpiboot mode</strong>:
          <ul>
            <li><strong>CM4 IO-Board</strong>: fit the jumper on <code>J2</code> (Disable eMMC Boot).</li>
            <li><strong>CM5 IO-Board</strong>: bridge the <code>nRPIBOOT</code> test pad (or set the fit-jumper where provided).</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Connect the <strong>USB-C slave port</strong> (not the host USB) to your machine.</li>
        <li>Power the board. RPi Imager (≥ 1.8.5) detects the CM as <em>"RPi"</em> mass storage via its built-in <code>rpiboot</code>.</li>
        <li>Flash as usual.</li>
        <li>Remove the jumper, re-power, boot.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="variants">
      <h2>🧩 Variants in this release</h2>
      <div class="cards">
        {% for m in manifests %}
        <article class="card">
          <header>
            <h2>{{ m.variant }}</h2>
            <span class="tag">{{ tag }}</span>
          </header>
          <p class="description">{{ m.description }}</p>
          <dl class="meta">
            <dt>Hostname</dt><dd><code>{{ m.hostname or '-' }}</code></dd>
            <dt>Targets</dt><dd>{{ m.targets | join(', ') }}</dd>
            <dt>Download size</dt><dd>{{ m.image.download_size | mib }} MiB</dd>
            <dt>Extracted size</dt><dd>{{ m.image.extract_size | mib }} MiB</dd>
            <dt>Release date</dt><dd>{{ m.release_date or '-' }}</dd>
          </dl>
          <div class="checksums">
            <div>
              <span class="label">SHA-256 (.img.xz)</span>
              <code>{{ m.image.download_sha256 }}</code>
            </div>
            <div>
              <span class="label">SHA-256 (.img)</span>
              <code>{{ m.image.extract_sha256 }}</code>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="{{ m.image.url }}">⬇ Download .img.xz</a>
            <a class="btn" href="{{ m.image.url }}.sha256">.sha256</a>
            <a class="btn" href="{{ m.image.url | replace('.img.xz', '.manifest.json') }}">manifest.json</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="security">
      <h2>🔐 Default credentials</h2>
      <p>These images ship with <strong>demo credentials</strong> - safe only on an isolated lab network:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>admin</code> password → <code>12345678</code></li>
        <li>WiFi PSK for <code>IOT @ BAUER-GROUP</code> → <code>12345678</code></li>
      </ul>
      <p>Bake real values at build time via <code>.env</code>, or change them post-flash with:</p>
      <pre><code>sudo bgrpiimage-setup password
sudo bgrpiimage-setup wifi "MyNet" "s3cret" DE
sudo bgrpiimage-setup ip eth0 static 10.0.0.5/24 10.0.0.1 1.1.1.1</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="meta-links">
      <h2>📚 More</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/{{ repo }}">Repository on GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/{{ repo }}/releases">All releases</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/{{ repo }}/blob/main/docs/hardware.md">Hardware reference</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/{{ repo }}/blob/main/docs/flash.md">Flashing guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/{{ repo }}/blob/main/docs/configuration.md">JSON configuration reference</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>© BAUER GROUP · <a href="https://github.com/{{ repo }}/blob/main/LICENSE">MIT</a> · generated {{ generated }}</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
